@node main "CYCAS DEMO - Help - Layers"
@toc "help.guide/main"


  About layers:


  CYCAS offers a technique of working  with  layers  which
  allows  you  to structure a drawing in up to 100 Layers.
  The usage of the layers may be compared with the  method
  of working with tracing paper.

  The different layers can be put on top of the other like
  tracing paper. There is always one active layer and  the
  others  can be placed in the background. You always draw
  on the active layer and the layers in the background are
  visible. Layers which are not visible are deactivated.

  You  can  name  all  layers.  When sending the output to
  printer or plotter only the  visible  layers  are  taken
  into account.

  Using  the  functions in the function list " Symbol" you
  can move the drawing elements between the  layers,  (via
  the Clipboard).


  The advantages of the layers in the background:

  All aspects of the drawing elements  of  the  background
  layers  can be "caught" with the Snap function. First of
  all this means that you can  use  the  elements  in  the
  background for designing the active layer.

  Futher on, you can use the elements in the background in
  order  to  modify  the  active elements. If you activate
  elements in  the  selection menu  the  elements  of  the
  layers in the background will not be affected.

  Ultimately, it is up to you how you best use the layers.

@endnode
